3.
USE AND DISCLOSURE
The personal information and other information collected from or about you is used for
                                the following purposes:
a)
To provide and manage the Service.
The information collected from or about you is used to provide the Services and features
                                to you, including to measure
                                and improve those Services and features; and to develop new products and services; to
                                improve and personalize your experience
                                with both online and off-line Services by delivering content you will find relevant and
                                interesting, including advertising and
                                marketing messages; to allow you to comment on content, and participate in online games,
                                contests, other promotions or rewards
                                programs; to provide you with customer support and to respond to inquiries. In order to
                                provide you with content and advertising
                                that is more interesting and relevant to you, the information from or about you may be
                                used to make inferences and predictions about
                                your potential areas of interest. When the information collected from or about you are
                                anonymized and does not identify you as a specific person,
                                it may be used for any purpose or share it with third parties, to the extent permitted
                                by applicable law.
b)
To allow service providers to assist in providing and managing the Services.
The information collected from or about you may be made available to certain third party
                                service providers, such as contractors, analytics
                                and other measurement companies, agents or sponsors who help analyze and understand your
                                use of the Services, and manage and/or provide the Services.
c)
To deliver video content.
In the ordinary course of our business, the information collected from or about you may
                                be shared with third parties in order to process
                                your requests and fulfill your orders for video content offered through the Services,
                                including, to provide you with access to localized
                                content and provide video content recommendations. For example, to process your request
                                to view certain authenticated video content through
                                the Services, information about you may be shared, including, without limitation, what
                                you have viewed, with your designated television content
                                provider and/or our third party service providers in order to authenticate and/or
                                authorize you to view authenticated video content through the Services.
d)
To contact you.
Certain promotional materials (e.g., newsletters or email updates) or notifications
                                related to the Services may periodically be sent to the
                                email address you provided to us at registration or for your account, on the basis
                                of your prior consent [when this is required under the applicable law]. If you want to
                                stop receiving promotional materials from the Service,
                                follow the unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of each email. There are certain
                                service notification emails that you may not opt-out of,
                                such as notifications of changes to the Services or policies. If you have installed a
                                mobile app and you wish to stop receiving push notifications,
                                you can change the settings either on your mobile device or through the app.
e)
To share with business partners.
Your information may be shared with business partners to permit them to send you
                                marketing communications consistent with your choices and subject to your prior
                                consent when this is required under the applicable law.
f)
To complete a merger or sale of assets.
If all or part of the Services are sold or made part of a sale or transfer of assets or
                                are otherwise involved in a merger or transfer
                                (including, without limitation, in connection with bankruptcy or a similar proceeding),
                                your information may be transferred to the party
                                or parties involved in the transaction as part of that transaction.
g)
To protect rights.
There may be instances when your information may be used or disclosed without providing
                                you with notice or choice, including situations
                                where there is a good faith belief that such use or disclosure is necessary in order to:
                                (i) protect, enforce, or defend legal rights,
                                privacy, safety, or property or employees, agents and contractors (including enforcement
                                of our agreements and our Terms of Use);
                                (ii) protect the safety, privacy, and security of users of the Services or members of
                                the public; (iii) protect against fraud or
                                for risk management purposes.
h)
To comply with legal obligations.
There may be instances when your information may be used or disclosed without 
                                providing you with notice or choice, including situations where there is a good
                                faith belief that such use or disclosure is necessary in order to (i) comply 
                                with the law or legal process; or (ii) respond to requests from public and 
                                government authorities.
For the above purposes, your information may be shared with Affiliates 
                                as described at the beginning of this Policy.
When we disclose personal information of UK & EU residents to third parties,
                                including our Affiliates, located outside the UK and/or the European Economic
                                Area (EEA) in countries which are not considered adequate by the European Commission,
                                we put in place appropriate and suitable safeguards designed to further protect your
                                personal information, if so required by the applicable data protection laws, such as 
                                standard contractual clauses adopted by the European Commission as per Articles 45 and 
                                46 of the EU General Data Protection Regulation 2016/679.
When the information collected from or about you does not - even indirectly - identify you 
                                as a specific person, that information may be used for any purpose
                                or share it with third parties.
