USER ACCESS AND CONTROL
If you would like to access, review, correct, update, suppress, or otherwise limit our
                                use of your personal information you have
                                previously provided directly to the Services, you may request to do so by contacting us
                                using the mechanisms provided below or by
                                logging in to the Services and updating your account information. We will try to comply
                                with your request as soon as reasonably practicable.
If you are a California resident
, you may request that we not share your personal information on a going-forward basis
                                with Affiliates or unaffiliated third parties
                                for their direct marketing purposes by contacting us using the mechanisms below. We will
                                try to comply with your request(s) as soon as reasonably practicable.
If you are an EU or UK resident
, you have certain rights in relation to your personal information, including the right
                                to:
a.
obtain confirmation as to whether or not your personal information exists, to receive a
                                copy of it and to be informed of its content,
                                source, as well as of further information, also available in this Privacy Policy, on the
                                purposes of processing of your personal information,
                                the categories its recipients, the existence of any automated decision-making, if any,
                                the envisaged period for which we will store it,
                                where possible, as well as the safeguards we have adopted for transfers outside the EEA;
b.
request the deletion, anonymization or restriction of the processing of your personal
                                information processed in breach of the applicable law;
c.
request that we limit the processing of your personal information where:
1.
You contest the accuracy of the personal information until the data controller has taken
                                sufficient steps to correct or verify its accuracy;
2.
the processing is unlawful but you do not want us to erase the data;
3.
we no longer need the personal information for the purposes of the processing, but you
                                require it for the establishment, exercise, or defense of legal claims; or
d.
withdraw your consent to the processing of personal information, if such processing is
                                based on your consent;
e.
object to the processing of your personal information, when the processing is based on
                                the legitimate interest of the data controller.
                                Upon your objection, the data controller shall no longer process the personal
                                information unless it demonstrates (i) compelling legitimate
                                grounds for the processing that override your interests, rights and freedoms or (ii)
                                that the processing of the data is for the establishment,
                                exercise or defense of legal claims;
f.
restrict the data controller’s processing of your personal information when that
                                processing is based on the data controller’s legitimate interests
                                and where you have objected to the processing on those grounds pending verification as
                                to whether we have compelling legitimate grounds to continue the processing;
g.
request the erasure of your personal information without undue delay;
h.
“data portability”, namely to receive an electronic copy of your personal information
                                that you have provided to us when (i) that data is being processed by automatic means,
                                and (ii) the processing is either based upon your consent or necessary for the
                                performance of a contract with you;
i.
lodge a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority of your country;
j.
in case of transfer of personal information to countries that do not offer an adequate
                                level of protection with respect to the protection of personal information,
                                you have the right at any time to request a copy of the safeguards adopted by TWDC to
                                protect your personal information.
To exercise the above rights, EU and UK residents should send a request to the contact
                                details indicated
section 9
below.
7.
DATA RETENTION
Your information will be retained for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes
                                outlined in this Privacy Policy unless a longer retention period is required or allowed
                                by applicable law.
Remember that even after you cancel your account, copies of some information from your
                                account may remain viewable in some circumstances where, for example, you have shared
                                information with Other Services. Because of the nature of caching
                                technology, your account may not be instantly inaccessible to others and there may be a
                                delay
                                in the removal of the content from elsewhere on the Internet and from search engines.
                                Backup information related to your account may also be retained on servers for some time
                                after cancelation for fraud detection or to comply with applicable law or internal
                                security policies. It is not always possible to completely remove or delete all of your
                                information
                                due to technical constraints, contractual, financial or legal requirements.
